Package grafiosch.repository

Interface GTNetJpaRepository

All Superinterfaces:
BaseRepositoryCustom<GTNet>, org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<GTNet,Integer>, GTNetJpaRepositoryCustom, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<GTNet,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<GTNet>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<GTNet,Integer>, UpdateCreateJpaRepository<GTNet>
public interface GTNetJpaRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNet,Integer>, GTNetJpaRepositoryCustom, UpdateCreateJpaRepository<GTNet>
Repository for managing GTNet domain configurations. Provides CRUD operations plus specialized queries for:
  • Finding broadcast targets (domains with any data exchange configured)
  • Finding active price providers (for consumer-side queries)
  • Looking up domains by URL (for handshake processing)
  • Finding open suppliers for various data exchange types
See Also:
  • for complex operations like message submission

    • findByAnyAcceptRequest

      @Query("SELECT DISTINCT g FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.acceptRequest > 0") List<GTNet> findByAnyAcceptRequest()
      Finds domains that have at least one GTNetEntity accepting requests. Used to determine broadcast targets for maintenance announcements and shutdown notices. Checks for acceptRequest > 0 (AC_OPEN=1 or AC_PUSH_OPEN=2).
      Returns:
      list of domains where at least one entity kind accepts requests

    • findByLastpriceConsumerUsageAndServerState

      @Query("SELECT DISTINCT g FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e JOIN e.gtNetConfigEntity c WHERE e.entityKind = 0 AND c.consumerUsage = :consumerUsage AND e.serverState = :serverState") List<GTNet> findByLastpriceConsumerUsageAndServerState(@Param("consumerUsage") byte consumerUsage, @Param("serverState") byte serverState)
      Finds domains that have a LAST_PRICE entity with specific consumer usage and server state. Used to find active price providers when this instance acts as a consumer.
      Parameters:
      consumerUsage - the priority level (0 = not used, higher = used with priority)
      serverState - the required server state (typically SS_OPEN = 4)
      Returns:
      list of domains matching the criteria for LAST_PRICE entity kind

    • findWithConfiguredExchange

      @Query("SELECT DISTINCT g FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e JOIN e.gtNetConfigEntity c WHERE c.exchange = true") List<GTNet> findWithConfiguredExchange()
      Finds GTNet entries that have data exchange configured. Returns entries where at least one GTNetEntity has a GTNetConfigEntity with exchange enabled. Used to determine which remote instances should be notified about this server's online/offline status.
      Returns:
      list of GTNet entries with configured data exchange

    • findPushOpenSuppliers

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, name="GTNet.findPushOpenSuppliers") List<GTNet> findPushOpenSuppliers()
      Finds push-open servers available for intraday price exchange. Returns domains where:
      • LAST_PRICE entity has acceptRequest = AC_PUSH_OPEN (2)
      • Server state is SS_OPEN (1)
      • Consumer usage priority > 0 (configured for use)
      • Server is online (serverOnline = SOS_ONLINE = 1)
      • Server is not busy
      Results are ordered by consumerUsage ASC (lower value = higher priority). Named query: GTNet.findPushOpenSuppliers
      Returns:
      list of push-open supplier domains ordered by priority

    • findOpenSuppliers

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, name="GTNet.findOpenSuppliers") List<GTNet> findOpenSuppliers()
      Finds open servers available for intraday price exchange. Returns domains where:
      • LAST_PRICE entity has acceptRequest = AC_OPEN (1)
      • Server state is SS_OPEN (1)
      • Consumer usage priority > 0 (configured for use)
      • Server is online (serverOnline = SOS_ONLINE = 1)
      • Server is not busy
      Results are ordered by consumerUsage ASC (lower value = higher priority). Named query: GTNet.findOpenSuppliers
      Returns:
      list of open supplier domains ordered by priority

    • findShareableServers

      @Query("SELECT g FROM GTNet g WHERE g.spreadCapability = true AND g.idGtNet <> :excludeId") List<GTNet> findShareableServers(@Param("excludeId") Integer excludeId)
      Finds domains that have spreadCapability enabled and are online. Used to build the server list for sharing with remote domains that have been granted access. Excludes the requesting server (by id) from the results.
      Parameters:
      excludeId - the GTNet ID to exclude (typically the requester's entry)
      Returns:
      list of shareable GTNet entries

    • findHistoryquotePushOpenSuppliers

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, name="GTNet.findHistoryquotePushOpenSuppliers") List<GTNet> findHistoryquotePushOpenSuppliers()
      Finds push-open servers available for historical price exchange. Returns domains where:
      • HISTORICAL_PRICES entity has acceptRequest = AC_PUSH_OPEN (2)
      • Server state is SS_OPEN (1)
      • Consumer usage priority > 0 (configured for use)
      • Server is online (serverOnline = SOS_ONLINE = 1)
      • Server is not busy
      Results are ordered by consumerUsage ASC (lower value = higher priority). Named query: GTNet.findHistoryquotePushOpenSuppliers
      Returns:
      list of push-open supplier domains for historyquotes ordered by priority

    • countByAnyAcceptRequest

      @Query("SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT g.idGtNet) FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.acceptRequest > 0") int countByAnyAcceptRequest()
      Counts GTNet entries where at least one GTNetEntity has acceptRequest > 0. Used to calculate TotalConnections variable for EvalEx expressions in GTNetMessageAnswer rules.
      Returns:
      count of GTNet entries with active data exchange capability

    • countByLastPriceAccepting

      @Query("SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT g.idGtNet) FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.entityKind = 0 AND e.acceptRequest > 0") int countByLastPriceAccepting()
      Counts GTNet entries where LAST_PRICE entity has acceptRequest > 0. Used to calculate ConnectionsLastPrice variable for EvalEx expressions in GTNetMessageAnswer rules.
      Returns:
      count of GTNet entries accepting LAST_PRICE requests

    • countByHistoricalAccepting

      @Query("SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT g.idGtNet) FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.entityKind = 1 AND e.acceptRequest > 0") int countByHistoricalAccepting()
      Counts GTNet entries where HISTORICAL_PRICES entity has acceptRequest > 0. Used to calculate ConnectionsHistorical variable for EvalEx expressions in GTNetMessageAnswer rules.
      Returns:
      count of GTNet entries accepting HISTORICAL_PRICES requests

    • countBySecurityMetadataAcceptingAndOnline

      @Query("SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT g.idGtNet) FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.entityKind = 2 AND e.acceptRequest > 0 AND g.serverOnline = 1") int countBySecurityMetadataAcceptingAndOnline()
      Counts GTNet entries where SECURITY_METADATA entity has acceptRequest > 0 and server is online. Used to determine if the GTNet security lookup feature should be available.
      Returns:
      count of GTNet entries accepting SECURITY_METADATA requests and online

    • findSecurityMetadataSuppliers

      @Query("SELECT DISTINCT g FROM GTNet g JOIN g.gtNetEntities e WHERE e.entityKind = 2 AND e.acceptRequest > 0 AND e.serverState = 1 AND g.serverOnline = 1 AND g.serverBusy = false") List<GTNet> findSecurityMetadataSuppliers()
      Finds domains that accept SECURITY_METADATA requests. Returns domains where:
      • SECURITY_METADATA entity has acceptRequest > 0 (AC_OPEN or AC_PUSH_OPEN)
      • SECURITY_METADATA entity has serverState = 1 (SS_OPEN)
      • Server is online (serverOnline = SOS_ONLINE = 1)
      • Server is not busy
      Returns:
      list of domains accepting security metadata requests
